cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks (SNNs) for visual feature learning, which falls under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV). The comparison with auto-encoders and the analysis of the results suggest that the paper also relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the discussion of hardware implementations and the need to address some bottlenecks in SNNs suggest a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
